702362f-a.title: Brooklyn: 4th Street (South) - Roebling Street
702362f-a.text:
South 4th Street, at and adjoining the NE.. corner of Roebling Street,
showing the First Presbyterian Church of Williamsburg, erected in 1848.
In the Brooklyn Atlas of 1880 the church structure was designated as the
Episcopal-Presbyterian; in 1908 as Roman Catholic; and in 1929 no denomination.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

702363f-a.title: Brooklyn: 4th Street (South) - Roebling Street
702363f-a.text:
207-215 South 4th Street, north side, at, adjoining and east of
Roebling Street. Also shown is Roebling Street, east side, north from
and including South 4th, to and including South 3rd Streets. The view
shows St. Mary, Queen of Angels, Roman Catholic Church.
October 19, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
